reviews.review_text: Set Closing Loser Thanx Andrew F.  Great audience recording.  In 21 years I have only found 1 & 1/2 shows from this run.  The Kaiser was my all time favorite Dead venue.  Even during this time there were shows with no line waiting to get in.  The park across was priceless.  Shows were generally winter time, so they had a cold dark atmosphere to the surroundings.  4 shows in 5 nights.  This was the only non holiday show.  The next nights were Valentines, Mardis Gras, and Chinese New Year's.  Each night had the auditorium in even more decoration.  I like the jam out of Gimme Some Lovin' and the Other One>Sat Night.  This show and run featured exceedingly short sets.  I am playing Gimme Some Lovin' thru Sat Night on my radio show this week.  Check it out.  Peace
